  "description": "A sonnet is a fourteen-line poem in [meter](./meter.md) (typically iambic pentameter) with a prescribed [rhyme](./rhyme.md) scheme and a structural [volta](./volta.md). It is one of the most durable fixed forms in the Western poetic tradition, originating in thirteenth-century Sicily and refined by Petrarch, Shakespeare, Milton, and many others.",
